==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Abductor
<hw>Ab*duc"tor</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>One who abducts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A muscle which serves to draw a
part out, or form the median line of the body; <as>as, the <ex>abductor
oculi</ex>, which draws the eye outward</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Abeam</ent>⟦br⟧
